# Cursor Rules Location

How to add new cursor rules to a project.

## Placement

1. Always place rule files in `PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/rules/`:

```txt
.cursor/rules/
├── your-rule-name.mdc
├── another-rule.mdc
└── ...
```

2. **Naming:** kebab-case filename, `.mdc` extension, descriptive purpose.

3. **Never** place rule files in the project root or in subdirectories outside `.cursor/rules/`.

## Directory structure

```txt
PROJECT_ROOT/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/
│       ├── your-rule-name.mdc
│       └── ...
└── ...
```

## Frontmatter

Every rule file starts with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
description: Short description of the rule's purpose (required)
globs: optional/path/pattern/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---
```

| Field | Purpose |
| ----- | ------- |
| `description` | Shown in rule pickers; keep it specific |
| `globs` | Limit when the rule applies (path patterns) |
| `alwaysApply` | `true` only for small, always-relevant rules |

## Rule body

1. Clear title and purpose
2. Detailed step-by-step instructions
3. Code examples (good vs bad when helpful)
4. Guidelines agents can follow while editing

## Example

```typescript
// Good example — follows project conventions
function goodExample() {
  // Implementation following guidelines
}

// Bad example — avoid this pattern
function badExample() {
  // Implementation not following guidelines
}
```

Follow [self-improvement.mdc](./self-improvement.mdc) for when to add or update rules.
